Auto-rotation should pause on hover.
Auto-rotation should permanently stop after any active user interaction.

Desktop: Permanently stop auto-rotation after the user has clicked on the carouselâ€™s interface controls.
Use dots and arrows that are big enough and that contrast with the underlying image. 
Never auto-rotate on mobile websites or for touch devices.
Touch devices: Support swipe gestures, in addition to any other UI controls.
Mobile devices: Ensure that the text in slides is still readable if you are scaling down artwork from the desktop.